The error occurs because you're using `java.time.LocalDate` which requires API level 26, but your app's minimum API level is 24. Here's how to fix it:

```kotlin:app/src/main/java/dev/eknath/barathtrainbookingremainder/MainActivity.kt
import java.time.LocalDate
import java.time.format.DateTimeFormatter
import androidx.core.os.BuildCompat
import java.text.SimpleDateFormat
import java.util.Date
import java.util.Calendar
import java.util.Locale

class MainActivity : ComponentActivity() {
 // ... existing code ...

 // Helper function to safely parse dates for API < 26
 private fun parseLocalDate(dateString: String?, defaultDaysToAdd: Long): LocalDate {
 if (dateString.isNullOrEmpty()) {
 return LocalDate.now().plusDays(defaultDaysToAdd)
 }

 if (android.os.Build.VERSION.SDK_INT >= android.os.Build.VERSION_CODES.O) {
 return LocalDate.parse(dateString)
 } else {
 // Fallback for older Android versions
 val sdf = SimpleDateFormat("yyyy-MM-dd", Locale.getDefault())
 val date = sdf.parse(dateString) ?: Date()
 val calendar = Calendar.getInstance()
 calendar.time = date
 return LocalDate.of(
 calendar.get(Calendar.YEAR),
 calendar.get(Calendar.MONTH) + 1,
 calendar.get(Calendar.DAY_OF_MONTH)
 )
 }
 }

 // ... existing code ...

 // In your composable
 composable(
 route = "add_reminder?date={date}&bookableDate={bookableDate}",
 // ... existing code ...
 ) { backStackEntry ->
 val dateString = backStackEntry.arguments?.getString("date")
 val bookableDateString = backStackEntry.arguments?.getString("bookableDate")

 // Parse the dates using helper function
 val selectedDate = parseLocalDate(dateString, 60)
 val bookableDate = parseLocalDate(bookableDateString, 90)

 // ... rest of your composable ...
 }
}
```

This approach adds a helper function that handles parsing dates safely across API levels. For API 26+ it uses `LocalDate.parse()` directly, while for older versions it uses the older date APIs and converts the result to LocalDate.

Note: You'll still need `java.time.LocalDate` at some point, which requires desugaring for API < 26. Make sure you have the Java 8+ API desugaring enabled in your build.gradle:

```gradle
android {
 compileOptions {
 coreLibraryDesugaringEnabled true
 sourceCompatibility JavaVersion.VERSION_1_8
 targetCompatibility JavaVersion.VERSION_1_8
 }
}

dependencies {
 coreLibraryDesugaring 'com.android.tools:desugar_jdk_libs:1.1.5'
 // other dependencies...
}
```"}]}

