The error message indicates that Gradle can't find the `org.jetbrains.kotlin.plugin.compose` plugin. This is because the Kotlin Compose plugin has been deprecated, and you should use the new Jetpack Compose Gradle plugin instead. Let me help you fix this:

## Fix Options:

### Option 1: Fix using Version Catalog (recommended)

Update your `libs.versions.toml` file:

```toml:gradle/libs.versions.toml
[versions]
ksp = "1.9.0-1.0.13"
agp = "8.9.0-alpha07"
kotlin = "1.9.22"
compose-compiler = "1.5.8" # Add this line, matching your Kotlin version compatibility

# ... other versions ...

[plugins]
android-application = { id = "com.android.application", version.ref = "agp" }
kotlin-android = { id = "org.jetbrains.kotlin.android", version.ref = "kotlin" }
# Remove the kotlin-compose plugin and add:
jetbrains-compose = { id = "org.jetbrains.compose", version = "1.5.11" } # OR
androidx-compose = { id = "androidx.compose.compiler", version.ref = "compose-compiler" }
